<p><b>Napkin folding</b> is a type of <a href="/wiki/Decorative_folding" title="Decorative folding">decorative folding</a> done with a <a href="/wiki/Napkin" title="Napkin">napkin</a>. It can be done as art or as a hobby. Napkin folding is most commonly encountered as a table decoration in fancy restaurants.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Typically, and for best results, a clean, pressed, and starched square cloth (linen or cotton) napkin is used.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> There are variations in napkin folding in which a rectangular napkin, a <a href="/wiki/Napkin_ring" title="Napkin ring">napkin ring</a>, a glass, or multiple napkins may be used.
</p>
